"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-09-28-being-mom-is-olympic-sport-rihanna\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Billionaire Barbadian singer Rihanna has opened up about motherhood.  According to the 36-year-old mother of two, being a \\\"boy mom\\\" is an Olympic sport.  Rihanna stated while sharing a clip of her first son, RZA, struggling to get out of the baby cot, via her X handle.  In the video, RZA eventually got out of the cot after several failed attempts.  She captioned the video; \\\"Being a boy mom is an Olympic sport \\u200d\\u2640\\ufe0f\\u200d\\u2640\\ufe0f.\\\"  DAILY POST recalls that Rihanna and her partner, A$AP Rocky, welcomed RZA on May 19, 2022, barely a year after they confirmed their relationship.  In August 2023, the couple welcomed their second son, Riot Ross.  Earlier this year, there were rumours that Rihanna was pregnant with her third child but she debunked the rumours in a chat with ET.  She, however, added that she would \\\"definitely\\\" have more kids.  In April, Rihanna told Interview Magazine that she had been looking for a female child but kept giving birth to boys.  \\\"I do not know what God wants, but I would go for more than two. I would try for my girl. But of course if it's another boy, it's another boy,\\\" she said.  I wrote hit songs for Wizkid - Skales  BBNaija S9: Married housemate, Kellyrae shares kiss with Dami [VIDEO]  Rihanna flees Los Angeles hours after Beverly Hills shooting  Drake beefing me over Rihanna - A$AP Rocky  My mom asked me to dump my ex-girlfriend for Rihanna - A$AP Rocky  I will love to feature Rihanna - Davido [VIDEO]  I am Rihanna's favourite artiste - Ayra Starr  Rihanna, A$AP Rocky confirm third pregnancy at 2025 Met Gala  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"